wytr.dialog.Hallfred.1.1.ddaf585d: Hey, we don't just let strangers use our people like that!
wytr.dialog.Adigard.6.1.c7d7958d: Welcome traveler, to our humble island...
wytr.dialog.Adigard.6.2.b0cad3e2: My people and I landed here many years ago. Unfortunately, our ship didn't make it...
wytr.dialog.Adigard.6.3.d4782c50: We tried to build a nation on these islands but became divided through the years.
wytr.dialog.Adigard.6.4.405fd03c: Because of this, we are fighting a useless war with our neighbours.
wytr.dialog.Adigard.6.5.13d44b2d: I believe we should try to pass a peace treaty, but I am afraid of getting killed if I leave the island...
wytr.dialog.Adigard.6.6.55ffd69f.1: Would you mind helping us? Talk to Hallfred about this treaty.
wytr.dialog.Adigard.6.6.55ffd69f.2: He lives on another ice island nearby.
wytr.dialog.Hallfred.5.1.0d14ddf5: Welcome traveler! What brings you to our island?
wytr.dialog.Hallfred.5.2.9195383d: Oh, I see that Adigard now sends strangers through his cowardice! Worried he'll get killed?
wytr.dialog.Hallfred.5.3.e4d460f7: This is the last time I'll repeat it: We will sign the peace treaty the day Adigard and his nation will return to us... the treasure.
wytr.dialog.Hallfred.5.4.22d8ba65: The one that they kept and hid from us after the shipwreck.
wytr.dialog.Hallfred.5.5.5c0f8e59.1: Pure gold, very valuable and rare!
wytr.dialog.Hallfred.5.5.5c0f8e59.2: Tell him I'll be waiting for it.
wytr.dialog.Hallfred.5.5.5c0f8e59.3: And none of that silly story again.
wytr.dialog.Adigard.7.1.24ae35d0: I should have expected that. Hallfred was always very greedy...
wytr.dialog.Adigard.7.2.024fc410: We tried to make him understand that we do not have the treasure, without much success.
wytr.dialog.Adigard.7.3.01970f49: ...You see, the reason why we became shipwrecked wasn't natural cause. We were attacked...
wytr.dialog.Adigard.7.4.a6f402fd: By whom? The undead. Ghosts and demons navigating a monstrous ship. They got us by surprise.
wytr.dialog.Adigard.7.5.3401c0e3: I believe they also stole our treasure during the attack.
wytr.dialog.Adigard.7.6.66a80dca: Would you help our nation come back together? Find this ship, and bring the treasure back to Hallfred so we can finally live in peace.
wytr.dialog.Adigard.7.7.a189fa34.2: That is where they attacked us many years ago. It should be easy to find, I'm sure they are anchored there in glory... Thank you.
wytr.dialog.Hallfred.4.1.6e5e5bea: Incredible! He actually delivered the treasure!
wytr.dialog.Hallfred.4.2.ead2b485: I suppose that means the end of the war between our nations!
wytr.dialog.Hallfred.4.3.a41d0589: This is a great day! Here, take this as a reward for helping our nation.
wytr.dialog.Hallfred.4.4.b24b888f: I'm sure you'll find a use for this helmet one day!
wytr.dialog.Adigard.1.1.9fad12af: Thank you so much for bringing peace between our nations!
wytr.dialog.Hallfred.2.1.37f601b6: Thank you again for bringing peace upon our islands.
wytr.dialog.Ankou.11.3.ace42e50: I challenge you to reach the final floor!
wytr.dialog.Ankou.11.4.477b6d81: Have you got what it takes to conquer it?
wytr.dialog.Ankou.11.5.1dfb24c5: Perhaps you would like to know the layout of the tower first? Hehehehe...
wytr.dialog.Ankou.11.6.54fba693: There are 7 floors in this tower, each with ten levels.
wytr.dialog.Ankou.11.7.5348aa90: Each floor has nine regular levels and one boss level.
wytr.dialog.Ankou.11.8.9ab65fea: To pass a regular level, you must collect five tokens from the challenge on that level, and one token from boss levels.
wytr.dialog.Ankou.11.9.920c531b: After you beat a whole floor, you will return here and you can begin the next one...
wytr.dialog.Ankou.11.10.030f028e: So, what do you say? Hehehe...
wytr.dialog.Ankou.11.11.6b532578.1: Turn left and head to the first floor...
wytr.dialog.Floormaster.1.1.08fc4992: I need five tokens from the enemies in this room as evidence that you are strong enough to ascend.
wytr.dialog.Floormaster.1.1.d2834ad3: I need one token from the boss in this room as evidence that you are strong enough to ascend.
wytr.dialog.Floormaster.1.1.0b22a600: Well done, adventurer, you have successfully completed this floor! You may proceed.
wytr.text.55a1900eaf8123c8676053f82df969: Five tokens are required to ascend to the next floor.
wytr.text.be522761ea7f8328929ada23433624: A boss token is required to ascend to the next floor.
wytr.text.8a0ff525d0d7e0c051ab641f19b5c7: A boss token is required to go through.
wytr.dialog.Ankou.6.1.ab571b12: You have completed my tower, I see...
wytr.dialog.Ankou.6.2.03390117: Did you enjoy Death? Many challengers certainly did. Her power is... unmatched, hehehe...
wytr.dialog.Ankou.6.3.77044b87: And you... You are unlike them all, yes? Few have managed to ascend these floors.
wytr.dialog.Ankou.6.4.3c152ac8: A tower of madness, fueled by Death herself... Quite a challenge, yes?
wytr.dialog.Ankou.6.5.a72e2f9b: You have joined us now, champion... Few can claim this victory as their own. Fewer still have held their mind.
wytr.dialog.Ankou.6.6.0902053f: For this honor... A reward, for you. You have truly earned it... Hehehehe...
wytr.dialog.ElectromagicExpert.1.1.a5931: Aah, this is bad, where's the keys to my toolbox?! Zenam said it was important, I need to find them!
wytr.dialog.Zenam.6.1.f72abb39: Aaah, no no no! This doesn't make any sense, what in the world is going on?! Nothing's working!
wytr.dialog.Zenam.6.2.f97f229b: Gweh, a visitor? Get out of here! The plant is shut down for maintenance- wait, are you the electromagic expert we're paying for?
wytr.dialog.Zenam.6.3.ced0dca9: You are, right? Right?! Cause we can't wait any longer! This system was supposed to be unbreakable, a flawless design!
wytr.dialog.Zenam.6.4.70610d83: We didn't even need to get Corkian consultation on this, we had this system all figured out ourselves, but now nothing's working right!
wytr.dialog.Zenam.6.5.f8ca49ea: You're seeing all these sparks and hearing all this crackling? We have no idea what could possibly be going wrong with this! That's why you're needed here!
wytr.dialog.Zenam.6.6.c515044b.1: We don't have much time until full meltdown! There is an entrance to the power plant
wytr.dialog.Zenam.6.6.c515044b.3: go there and meet with the
wytr.dialog.Zenam.1.1.c2057a87.1: Come on now, hurry! There is an entrance to the power plant opposite the bank, go there and meet with the
wytr.text.8e010ddc148265ce279b73e4d086f2: The crackling and humming gets louder..
wytr.text.54947e8d130050c4f960a4c157d243: You hear a buzzing sound, so you don't enter.
wytr.dialog.HeadEngineer.5.1.97c33402: Whew, finally Zeman found a guy for the job. I told him weeks ago this was a two-person task...
wytr.dialog.HeadEngineer.5.2.0d00566b: Wait, it's Zenam? Eh, what does it matter? You knew who I was talkin' about. Lemme give you the lowdown real fast.
wytr.dialog.HeadEngineer.5.3.e5f7e128: About a month ago, there was a big blackout, and the generator here started acting up. Power surges, appliances overloading...heck, some of our lights turned purple!
wytr.dialog.HeadEngineer.5.4.2778a30e: My grandfather and his engineers jury-rigged this whole system. A reset should fix all this, but as a security measure, I need to be here to oversee the reset.
wytr.dialog.HeadEngineer.5.5.a5e070be.1: So that's your job- get through the system and
wytr.dialog.HeadEngineer.5.5.a5e070be.3: These holes'll lead you around the generator rooms. Better get going!
wytr.dialog.HeadEngineer.1.1.45d3681f.1: I have to stay put, so get through the system and
wytr.dialog.HeadEngineer.1.1.45d3681f.2: find the reset button for me. These holes are teleporters
wytr.dialog.HeadEngineer.1.1.45d3681f.3: that'll lead you around the generator rooms.
wytr.text.bac7b68fad93662ed6856a6c975e4d: You can hear a soft humming coming from the walls.
wytr.text.2c0c7e08b2b08f1b89ea8d5f1e554a: You feel powerful electricity rushing through your body as you enter the room.
wytr.narration.2b6325d94c1acd1dbf8101b37: Maybe you can find a way to reset the system. That ought to do it...
wytr.dialog.HeadEngineer.5.1.829a2602: Alright, that should do it- Ah, you're back. The system reset just fine, like I said. Everything should be winding down now.
wytr.dialog.HeadEngineer.5.2.7d009f90: It's purging the excess energy now- might have a few more power surges and crackles for a while, but it'll go back to normal soon enough.
wytr.dialog.HeadEngineer.5.3.4e8847af: Hm? What, there was a bug in the system? ...what, are you asleep or something? Of course there was a bug, we just fixed it!
wytr.dialog.HeadEngineer.5.4.dc6ce501: Well, anyways, Zebra should have our payment all settled. You go on ahead- I still need to stay down here to make sure everything stays smooth.
wytr.dialog.HeadEngineer.5.5.079e4994: ...oh, it's Zenam? D'you really care about getting his name right, or what? Anyways, the exit's through the water cooling system, it hooks up to the sewer exit.
wytr.dialog.Zenam.4.1.33d2135d: Whew...welcome back. The power is back online- Everything is running at full capacity again. I think the system is just running excess through right now.
wytr.dialog.Zenam.4.2.a5c5fe3b: Glad you got here when you did though- some phony came through saying he was the expert. Clearly he was just here to take your contract money...
wytr.dialog.Zenam.4.3.fea3c68e: Though, I was panicking so much I probably would've believed him... Speaking of which, here's your cut of the pay, and something extra for the trouble.
wytr.dialog.Zenam.4.4.6b08a1e1: Here's to hoping that the system won't run into any more trouble in the future. I don't want to be faced with an impending cataclysm like that again...
wytr.dialog.Zenam.1.1.cadb9f3d: Oh, that experience gave me gray hairs... I sincerely hope there won't ever be bugs in the system like that for the rest of my life.
wytr.dialog.ElectromagicExpert.1.1.24a97: I still can't believe it, a human has done
emeralds... Just because I lost my keys...
wytr.text.3a7819137116ec42f9316ff91dc159: What was that? It seems to have landed nearby, maybe you should go investigate.
wytr.dialog.Agent.5.1.84f4a273: Hey you! Human. What are you doing here?
wytr.dialog.Agent.5.2.91fcf9a0: Under Villager law any extra terrestrial or extra voidal entities are prohibited and owned by the state.
wytr.dialog.Agent.5.3.62841c42: Seeing as you are new to the land, I can't see you being prosecuted, especially a Ragni Guard.
wytr.dialog.Agent.5.4.c6a0b23a: This meteor is different to what we've seen before. We suspect that direct contact with the meteor is dangerous.
wytr.dialog.Agent.5.5.1928e42f: The magical radiation doesn't seem to be affecting you at all though. Do you not feel anything? Perhaps you could help me locate it.
wytr.text.f5625f1c088642cc4d8df3dbd5d32c: It seems like the meteor crashed into a cave.
wytr.text.137c3bf679eb81653503e4aa2ec061: The meteor shard is radiating an odd and unfamiliar magical energy
wytr.text.4c2226e303e3b6c36672e865801fd3: The cave is collapsing! Find a way out, quickly.
wytr.text.7cc13b216a2f98a5877191ec7343c4: Someone stole a piece of meteorite. It's unstable and dangerous...
wytr.text.6c6b23e2c31c597620088e2f496c9c: A weird trail leads off to the east, maybe you can retrieve the meteor if you follow it?
wytr.dialog.Thief.2.1.f5d61ee7: What is... this feeling... No I won't listen..
wytr.dialog.Agent.2.1.f008059d: Hello again. Did you find the meteor down there? No? Maybe go back and try to find it?
wytr.dialog.Agent.4.1.09a84be2: Hello again. Did you find the meteor down there? Why on earth are you holding some?!
wytr.dialog.Agent.4.2.a56401df: I see. This material is incredibly rare and magically powerful. Meteors fall all over Gavel and come in a variety of colours and potency.
wytr.dialog.Agent.4.3.70593cfb: We don't fully understand them, but we know they are dangerous. Every scientist who has studied them has lost their minds.
wytr.dialog.Agent.4.4.ba9a6476: The meteors hold many secrets and powers, maybe the ones we need to end your war. Thank you, here's a small reward for helping us.
wytr.dialog.Agent.1.1.f0c1acc2: Thank you again for your help!
wytr.dialog.Fredris.3.1.e810dcab: I’m having trouble with the fish in our lake recently and I am sure the problem lies within the lake itself.
wytr.dialog.Fredris.3.2.7d1b04ef: I would like to commission you to investigate, but since it's freezing cold in our lake you need something to protect you. I heard the people in Maltic on the coast of Wynn have something that can help you.
wytr.dialog.Fredris.3.3.e0b9ca6e.1: Would you mind coming back with a
wytr.dialog.Fredris.3.3.e0b9ca6e.3: ? I think that should be everything you need.
wytr.dialog.Fredris.2.1.55a7dbc5.1: What is this thing supposed to be? You know, I would really appreciate your help, but this
wytr.dialog.Fredris.2.1.55a7dbc5.3: does not look like it's going to keep you protected.
wytr.dialog.Fredris.2.2.7cd1690c.1: Would you mind heading to our local armour merchant and buying one of our
wytr.dialog.Fredris.2.2.7cd1690c.3: ? I don't want you to drown. Just come back with the helmet and I will tell you about my problem.
wytr.dialog.Fredris.1.1.d455ce4f: Have you found the issue yet? I'm still waiting!
wytr.dialog.Fredris.1.1.6763e10b: Are you really trying to dive in that without the proper equipment?
wytr.text.fa62d680ab2a3af30199f4fbdc673f: Find out what the issue under the lake is..
wytr.dialog.Calamaro.5.1.dbce98d0: Who are you? You don't look like one of those villagers we stole the fi... Wait, they didn't send you to retrieve "their" fish, did they?
wytr.dialog.Calamaro.5.2.668a4182: For years we let them share the lake with us, the actual inhabitants of it, we were modest and took what we needed, we let them catch the rest. But then they went too far, they caught too much.
wytr.dialog.Calamaro.5.3.a7084763.1: We didn't have enough to eat, we were forced to steal their fish, we would have starved otherwise. And now they want their fish,
wytr.dialog.Calamaro.5.3.a7084763.3: fish back? We can't do that, I hope you understand.
wytr.dialog.Calamaro.5.4.53a01c49.1: However we don't have to fight over the fish in the lake, we just need a
wytr.dialog.Calamaro.5.4.53a01c49.3: , that would be enough, nothing else. We never wanted to steal the fish.
wytr.dialog.Calamaro.5.5.b161aa9f.1: If you want to help us and the villagers,
wytr.dialog.Calamaro.5.5.b161aa9f.2: just follow the stream that flows into this lake to the south,
wytr.dialog.Calamaro.5.5.b161aa9f.3: you will find the best fishing ground there. The pufferfish should be around there too.
wytr.dialog.Calamaro.1.1.7c93d4c3: I wish we could have avoided this whole scenario.
wytr.dialog.Gernald.5.1.46165a81: Oh you look a bit lost, let me help you, I've lived here for a long time, I know every corner and every snowflake.
wytr.dialog.Gernald.5.2.ed8f926b.3: ? Hmm I heard that name before, my friend, Strato, told me about it years ago. If I remember correctly it is infinite, you can feed every single person in all the provinces from this single fish.
wytr.dialog.Gernald.5.3.55321abc.1: Sadly Strato is no longer alive. He used to work and live at
wytr.dialog.Gernald.5.3.55321abc.2: the woodcutting camp northwest of Nesaak.
wytr.dialog.Gernald.5.3.55321abc.3: We always met here, caught fish and told each other stories. I really miss those times...
wytr.dialog.Gernald.5.4.fd013c5f: Maybe you can find some sort of bait there, he had some of the best bait I have ever seen. You should be able to acquire some and throw it in the water, maybe that will attract the pufferfish.
wytr.dialog.Gernald.5.5.dac18742: Can I ask you something? As you might see I'm not the richest guy, or the youngest. If you manage to catch that fish, could you hand it over? I know we just met but you seem like somebody who would help an old man.
wytr.dialog.Gernald.2.1.1b1b5dc3: Your best bet is to go to the woodcutting camp northwest of Nesaak, there should be some bait there. Just catch it in the river by the dock when you get it.
wytr.dialog.Gernald.2.2.d4f84da3: I know you might need the pufferfish for something else, but please think about giving it to me. It would warm my heart.
wytr.dialog.Calamaro.2.1.ba6c0f53: You found a pufferfish! Who would have thought such a small thing could solve our problem. I will start bringing back the fish immediately, but first we will have a nice hot soup. Please take this as payback for your services.
wytr.dialog.Calamaro.2.2.2b91bab7: You can trade it at the shop right over there, it's hard to miss. I will give you a last advise, you don't want to eat that slimy fish.
wytr.dialog.Gernald.1.1.bd83ccb0: You decided to give me the fish? I wish Strato was still around, he would be so amazed. I can't show you how much this means to me, but take this little gift please, promise me to never change.
wytr.dialog.Fredris.2.1.4537d1d6: Oh you are done with whatever you were doing? I heard you ran around the whole place, I don't know if you were the right person to ask for help...
wytr.dialog.Fredris.2.2.f01a7726: I will just ask the next one who comes around, no need to have you run around all day. Take this, I appreciate your effort.
wytr.dialog.Telvu.9.1.1c19c3ad: Ah, a member of the Ragni army. We're trying to gain entry to this frozen barrow. We could use your aid.
wytr.dialog.Telvu.9.2.ed2d579c: Are you familiar with the story of Theorick and Nesaak?
wytr.dialog.Telvu.9.3.46ff94a8: Probably not. Well, you see, Nesaak was not always frozen.
wytr.dialog.Telvu.9.4.8238f65f: During Theorick's time, this place was like the Wynn plains, warm and arable.
wytr.dialog.Telvu.9.5.e4f0a5b7: For some reason, Theorick Twain used his immense power to freeze the land before exiling himself here.
wytr.dialog.Telvu.9.6.9d4e3214: We need to find out why so we can reverse this spell. Presumably, the source of that spell's magic would be within here.
wytr.dialog.Telvu.9.7.e5a65093.3: you heard of a place called Time Valley? We could use it to go back in time, to try to learn more about this barrier.
wytr.dialog.Telvu.9.8.1088e3d0.2: a way, at least. There are laws to this sort of magic. For one, you need an item from the specific time we want to see. Second, you can witness the past, not change it.
wytr.dialog.Telvu.9.9.2e6eceb1.2: on display in the Nesaak bank.
wytr.dialog.Telvu.9.9.2e6eceb1.3: Presumably, it should work for what we need. Could you retrieve it somehow?
wytr.dialog.Telvu.2.2.2a122eed: If you don't remember what I said, I remember you writing something in your book. Try looking there.
wytr.narration.bb94416ddc418108041e61970: You should head back to the mage with the wand.
wytr.dialog.Telvu.5.1.414494b7: Aha, quick job. I see you've got the wand. Must've needed a sharp tongue to get the bankers to give it up.
wytr.dialog.Telvu.5.2.383f8c39: Now, it is a long walk to Time Valley. Needn't take that walk, though, as I can teleport you there. Hopefully.
wytr.dialog.Telvu.5.3.dab91a7f: Once you're there, enter the Temple of Time. You should know what to do once you are there. Careful dealing with time travel, friend... No idea what you might find.
wytr.dialog.Telvu.5.5.a4c35b11: Should anything go wrong, I'll stay here to teleport you back to the temple.
wytr.narration.29b60eb9fab3bde407f202eb9: This is the Temple of Time...
wytr.narration.633f65453289b55b315b9e5be: Here you can visit the memories of this land...
wytr.narration.2fc9e6c77ca16464b37961eee: The altar requires an item from the time you desire to access...
wytr.narration.d4c045409252c371877527c20: You can not return until your goal is fulfilled...
wytr.narration.5017c80f40e4ada36d96ce52d: You will access a memory as if you were present, but when you return it will be as if you were never there.
wytr.dialog.Psern.7.2.9481ef17: Woah, your weaponry and armour is so advanced!
wytr.dialog.Psern.7.3.a87a79e9: Are you another Twain? Only the Twains know magic like that.
wytr.dialog.Psern.7.5.c8030c16: He's busy fighting in the war, shouldn't you be doing the same?
wytr.dialog.Psern.7.6.1962e9bb.2: There was some kind of emergency.
wytr.dialog.Psern.7.7.edb040ef: We've been fighting the corruption for years, it seems like it might finally engulf Nesaak.
wytr.dialog.Psern.2.1.ef2e392a: If you need to speak to Theorick, he's on a mission in the western part of the forest.
wytr.dialog.Theorick.15.1.a3553151: I could've sworn she had gone this way... Oh, what now, more imbeciles? This forest isn't safe to travel!
wytr.dialog.Theorick.15.2.502afa5f: If you need help, lodge a complaint with the guards. I'm busy and I can't exactly break away from saving this god-blessed province to chill your milk!!
wytr.narration.b288c31ae6ce4a5a1e69584ab: You should stick around to find out how to reverse the spell.
wytr.dialog.Theorick.15.3.2e79e97c: Are your ears full of wax?! I said-
wytr.dialog.Theorick.15.4.b14838aa: Urgh, the things followed you! See what happens?! STAND ASIDE.
wytr.dialog.Theorick.15.5.4d499afc: As though I needed TWO people to save! Now get out of here, I have to find that woman who went missing!
wytr.dialog.???.15.6.b4da8242: HEEEELP! I can't outrun them!!! Guards! Someone!!
wytr.dialog.Theorick.15.7.a24fadb0: Whuh! That's her voice! Where is she?! I just cleared this area!
wytr.dialog.Theorick.15.9.882154dc: Ugh, is she dragging them over from the west?! You there, If you don't want to end up frozen, GET BEHIND ME, NOW!!
wytr.dialog.Theorick.15.10.18ad1bce: Phew... You're out of danger now. If you hadn't left town, though, you wouldn't have been IN any danger at all!
wytr.dialog.Theorick.15.11.f1f84003: Don't bother apologizing to me, just get back to town. Now.
wytr.dialog.Theorick.15.12.a76cbb11: Next time you feel like picking flowers in the forest or whatever you were doing, remember you have a life to live, hm?!
wytr.dialog.Theorick.15.13.43a9e1ae.1: Every day, more corrupteds, more deaths... There is only one thing for it. I have to tackle it myself. Cut the
wytr.dialog.Theorick.15.14.99559c2f: Still here? Well, listen up. Myself and a few others are planning something risky. Damned be it if our minds are lost, I need to go through that portal.
wytr.dialog.Theorick.15.15.57b38294.1: You look heavily geared, so I'm conscripting you. Meet us at our base, immediately.
wytr.dialog.Theorick.3.1.b4c25f74: Well, I'll give you this. You're prompt to listen to orders, at least. We're headed to the Roots of Corruption.
wytr.dialog.Theorick.3.2.fe381d7a: The last man that entered the portal and returned became Bak’al... But if there is even a fraction of a chance this could work, we must take it at this point.
wytr.dialog.Theorick.3.3.70274d5e: Let's get moving. We'll be taking no breaks on the trip, so I hope you were prepared.
wytr.dialog.Theorick.3.1.5ec77137: Now. The sheer cold I command can stave off corruption itself. Somehow I doubt any of you can say the same. I'll go in alone.
wytr.dialog.Theorick.3.2.1cf7a09b: When I enter... If I had to make an assumption, corrupteds will swarm the portal after me. Your job? Slay them. I can't have distractions in there.
wytr.dialog.Theorick.3.3.11e36159: You will not be leaving your post here until I exit that portal. Understood?
wytr.dialog.Theorick.4.2.2ae04a09: ...no, no, no no no NO!! DAMN IT ALL!!
wytr.dialog.Theorick.4.3.e2e173fb: You know what happened?! I lost!! I will destroy the province if I turn completely! GET AWAY, NOW! DO YOU HEAR ME?! RUN!!
wytr.dialog.Theorick.4.4.fdfd7942.1: I... C-calm yourself, Theorick...don't...don't lose yourself to it...there'
wytr.dialog.Theorick.8.2.d01f4294.3: up. Listen to me. If I
wytr.dialog.Theorick.8.3.f58251e0.1: I won't last, you can tell... Right now...killing me is an impossibility, you
wytr.dialog.Theorick.8.3.f58251e0.3: Agh, GET OUT OF MY MIND!!
wytr.dialog.Theorick.8.4.bcad701d.1: Gaaah... Tell...everyone. I will freeze this place. I...t-too fargone. It needs time to
wytr.dialog.Theorick.8.5.d246f724.8: will surely claim some. Please, let them know why...
wytr.dialog.Theorick.8.6.f2f751a7.1: If I have learned anything from that
wytr.dialog.Theorick.8.6.f2f751a7.4: Mael...deaths without reason lets spirits linger. I would...prefer against giving him a harder time.
wytr.dialog.Theorick.8.7.188d07d9.1: K-keep advancing. Your things, if everyone was as strong as
wytr.dialog.Theorick.8.7.188d07d9.3: may stand a chance. This could end me, in time, once I am weaker.
wytr.dialog.Theorick.8.8.e3d621e7.1: Let it be known...Theorick Twain is not dead.
wytr.dialog.Theorick.8.8.e3d621e7.5: until future days. Here, in this accursed place. Find
wytr.dialog.Telvu.9.1.153b8f1f: You must have succeeded, or you would be yet in the memory of the past. I can feel some potent magic on you.
wytr.dialog.Telvu.9.2.5181b9c1: So, you met Theorick? He was always said to have fallen from heroism after the great freezing.
wytr.dialog.Telvu.9.3.0bd0d856.3: you receive it from the Temple of Time? How
wytr.dialog.Telvu.9.3.0bd0d856.7: is impossible, given what we know!
wytr.dialog.Telvu.9.4.7973b118: It unfreezes the entrance, you say...and...Th-Theorick...gave...he...what...? This raises so many more questions! Unless there was some other force at play...
wytr.dialog.Telvu.9.5.ba5f4d0f: Well, ruminating on that will not help. Were you able to figure out why it was Theorick froze this place, at least?
wytr.dialog.Telvu.9.6.3aba14c5.4: magic staves off corruption...? It is true that this place has seen less corrupted threats than other places in the province...
wytr.dialog.Telvu.9.7.5abd0ba3.1: Dear gods... We've had it all wrong this whole time... This was to protect
wytr.dialog.Telvu.9.7.5abd0ba3.3: surely he would have told someone his intentions if he was of that sound a mind!
wytr.dialog.Telvu.9.8.0e87e344: All this time, spent buried alive, wrestling with the corruption. The thought horrifies you, as well, judging by your face. Killing him would be a mercy.
wytr.dialog.Telvu.9.9.ee077f55: Here. Use this. It may help protect you within the Ice Barrows... Please, soldier. Be Theorick's guardian angel. Free him from this torment.
wytr.dialog.Telvu.1.1.c9ce15b6.1: It will be dangerous...perhaps your toughest fight
wytr.dialog.Telvu.1.1.c9ce15b6.3: it must be done. If you need time to prepare, do so. But you must end Theorick's pain.
wytr.dialog.Piere.7.1.b5a59e79: Oh sweet baby bovine, my house, what am I going to do? Wait, who are you?
wytr.dialog.Piere.7.2.d30521eb: Oh, a Human. Did the Llevigar authorities send you?
wytr.dialog.Piere.7.3.df72b975: Detective Jackson has already been here. Not that he's doing anything useful.
wytr.dialog.Piere.7.4.db047235: An Orc managed to find some fire-imbued magical axe and burned down my house! Jackson didn't even call a firefighter!!
wytr.dialog.Piere.7.5.a61e71e2: I don't know what to do, but maybe if you find Detective Jackson, you can kick his sorry rear into gear...
wytr.dialog.Piere.7.6.7a52c6c2: The Orcs are already savage brutes. If they really have their hands on magical weapons, we're all in trouble!
wytr.dialog.Piere.7.7.14f5043b.1: I believe Detective Jackson is by his cart "planning his next move." He's not far from here.
wytr.dialog.Piere.1.1.f99a9d9d.1: Jackson is twiddling his thumbs off to the southeast.
wytr.dialog.DetectiveJackson.10.1.fddffd: How can I go about this...? I can't get involved myself, and they won't let me near... Wait, a human?
wytr.dialog.DetectiveJackson.10.2.0a8db5: do you MEAN "what am I doing?" This is a delicate situation! I need to- wait...actually, you might just be the help I need.
wytr.dialog.DetectiveJackson.10.3.2830da: I'll give you the lowdown- we believe the orcs stole magical weaponry from within Llevigar, particularly a flaming axe.
wytr.dialog.DetectiveJackson.10.4.4419fa: However, there's a loophole in the ceasefire we had enacted with the Orcs. Theft isn't considered an act of aggression...
wytr.dialog.DetectiveJackson.10.5.fcc230: And that means my hands are tied. Humans, however, were not mentioned in the notes, so you'll need to retrieve it.
wytr.dialog.DetectiveJackson.10.6.ddff75: Our only saving grace is that it'll be impossible for them to replicate its power- Orcs are hilariously inept at magic.
wytr.dialog.DetectiveJackson.10.7.56407f: But, to the primary problem- You've probably seen how many orc camps are around here. Searching will take a long while...
wytr.dialog.DetectiveJackson.10.8.a6281a: My only leads are that the "Sablestone" and "Loamsprout" camps seem to be celebrating recently. Best to start there, yes?
wytr.dialog.DetectiveJackson.10.9.4ee362: Just to review- You need to search those two camps for the Axe of Llevigar, and then return it to me if you find it.
wytr.dialog.DetectiveJackson.10.10.52bd4: Sablestone is to the north, and Loamsprout to the south.
They will be guarded, so don't be afraid to knock some heads.
wytr.dialog.DetectiveJackson.1.1.99e6a80: That orc ran towards the lake!! Get it, get it before it runs someplace else!!
wytr.text.489fc27d3856b8d6a74831f2564119: This does not seem like the weapon. It's just a heavy-looking wooden stick.
wytr.text.28a9634b7ff1759128d005bd1c82f9: This does not seem like the weapon. It's just a potato..?
wytr.text.57420bad7b15206f2f4730aef18792: This camp doesn't seem to have the weapon either. Maybe Detective Jackson knows what to do next?
wytr.dialog.DetectiveJackson.9.1.0e3b7f7: I see no axe in your hands, so I should assume neither Sablestone or Loamsprout had it.
wytr.dialog.DetectiveJackson.9.2.62cd4ee: Wait, really? A stick was the most powerful weapon they had? And Loamsprout...threw their dinner at you...?
wytr.dialog.DetectiveJackson.9.3.bc063d3: I can't believe this! How are those...those THINGS outsmarting us?! Are they shuffling the axe between camps?
wytr.dialog.DetectiveJackson.9.4.2174f55: There are over a dozen camps between the Orcs and Goblins that they could be swapping it between!
wytr.dialog.DetectiveJackson.9.5.25e7720: What if the GOBLINS get a hold of it?! They're the cleverest by half of all of them, so that could actually be a threat!
wytr.dialog.DetectiveJackson.9.6.3da4bd9: Searching the camps one by one will be far too slow, gah!! How am I going to fix this?!
wytr.dialog.DetectiveJackson.9.7.036d2c5: There's Earthpit, and Cliffhearth, Shineridge and Stonecave, Sunspark, Mudspring, Holehold, I-
wytr.dialog.???.9.8.c448c1bf: Fire! Stop!! I hold magic cutter! LISTEN TO POXPER!!
wytr.dialog.DetectiveJackson.9.9.16b83fe: I- I can't believe it, that has to be the one!
wytr.dialog.Poxper.1.1.f2a1215d: Uthniiazek! Uthniiazek!! WHY NO LISTEN TO POXPER?
wytr.dialog.Poxper.3.1.3c0c578e: Stupid Villager magic thing! Why fire no listen?
wytr.dialog.Poxper.3.3.d007f2d2: Hraahah! Poxper control fire! Fire- kill human with Poxper! Uthniiazek! Azektoluth!
wytr.dialog.DetectiveJackson.4.1.6a5f7aa: That looks like the Axe of Llevigar to me! Blue finish, hot to the touch- well done! What Orc boss had stolen it?
wytr.dialog.DetectiveJackson.4.2.40b37b7: Poxper? That...hm. This could be bad. I've heard that name, and he's a fairly prolific Orc chief. You killed him, right?
wytr.dialog.DetectiveJackson.4.3.5c22c9f: Mmm... Hopefully that Veretel won't catch wind of it. Regardless, you've done a great service for Villager-kind!
wytr.dialog.DetectiveJackson.4.4.0bfb629: Here's your compensation for that. Thank you for the aid!
wytr.dialog.DetectiveJackson.2.1.e90c3ef: Come to think of it, was that Poxper using... No, he couldn't have been casting magic, he had to have just been using the Axe's runewords...
wytr.dialog.DetectiveJackson.2.2.1dd15c8: ...wait, how would he have known the runewords? Are those orcs smarter than we've given them credit for...?
wytr.text.3e9757d4df1437778a085e4932b7d4: The frozen building teleports you out, do not enter unless you are required.
wytr.dialog.Tarod.9.1.21a3d87f: You're one of those soldier types, right? My name is Tarod, and I could really use your assistance here.
wytr.dialog.Tarod.9.2.147fbbaa.1: Years ago, I met a very powerful and legendary warrior by the name of Bob. Yes,
wytr.dialog.Tarod.9.3.218edeac: It's safe to say he was a very, well, admirable man. Him and I slowly became close friends over the years.
wytr.dialog.Tarod.9.4.e6211e67: That is, until one night, he vanished without a trace. The accepted story is that he was murdered by a pack of ravenous wolves...
wytr.dialog.Tarod.9.5.919f05a2.1: Now, I don't buy that story, but... look, the point here is that he's gone now, and I want to find out where the hell he ended up. That depressing zombie lumbering around Ragni
wytr.dialog.Tarod.9.6.9df33d22: I believe he died in this area, and I have been looking for his body for quite a while now, with... less than success.
wytr.dialog.Tarod.9.7.41613c8a.2: tomb lies somewhere east of Nesaak,
wytr.dialog.Tarod.9.7.41613c8a.3: but I've never been able to find it. This is where I need you to help me out, yeah?
wytr.dialog.Tarod.9.8.1cceba33.1: Do you think you could help me out here?
wytr.dialog.Tarod.9.8.1cceba33.3: and report back to me if you see anything noteworthy.
wytr.dialog.Tarod.9.9.eec3431d: I'd be eternally grateful if you could help me uncover my old friend's true story.
wytr.dialog.Tarod.1.1.1a90d7b7: Brr... It's a little bit cold out there, don't you think?
wytr.text.a3b7e7409b7ad0688f3c04c729502b: A strange force prevents you from entering. You can hear some soft laments in the distance...
wytr.dialog.Tarod.6.1.710cb65a: Welcome back. Did you find anything worthwhile?
wytr.dialog.Tarod.6.2.765630c1: Oh? Yeah, that definitely sounds like the tomb! Were you able to see what's inside?
wytr.dialog.Tarod.6.3.087214c7: No? There's... a magical barrier? Great... just GREAT...
wytr.dialog.Tarod.6.4.e889cde5: I have a feeling whoever made that tomb didn't want anyone attempting to get to him, but... Forget it, we have no other options. This is the only way we can place Bob's soul to rest for good.
wytr.dialog.Tarod.6.5.0f7514c1: Listen, I have a guy who can help us out. His name is Wedyf, a sorcerer type. If anyone could get rid of that barrier, it would be him.
wytr.dialog.Tarod.6.6.11907bf6.2: a small town close to Almuj.
wytr.dialog.Wedyf.10.1.3bb29b54: Welcome traveler. Are you looking for something?
wytr.dialog.Wedyf.10.2.3bb0d6f5: Ooh, it has been a long time since I've released an undead...
wytr.dialog.Wedyf.10.3.b4fc2845: The spirit of your dead friend must still be somewhere in this world. This is why we are unable to get close to his body. Soul magic works in mysterious ways.
wytr.dialog.Wedyf.10.4.2c97427e: Don't worry, I can do it. I've heard a little bit of Bob's story before. What a tragedy. His own infallible protection used against him...
wytr.dialog.Wedyf.10.6.f6d8f1d8: ...Anyways, there's no need to lament on the past. Now, we need two items. The first is something from Bob himself. The other is the last thing that made his blood drop.
wytr.dialog.Wedyf.10.7.2fa3d18b: Out past the other side of Detlas, near Nesaak, there are some arches in the mountains. An old florist lives in a house close by. She has a rose that Bob had once cut himself on.
wytr.dialog.Wedyf.10.8.48d000ad: I will warn you, though; she was corrupted some time ago. It may not be that easy to take the rose, so do be prepared.
wytr.dialog.Wedyf.10.9.f0d71690.1: Secondly... something of Bob's. I've heard rumors of a visage of him wandering around Ragni,
wytr.dialog.Wedyf.10.9.f0d71690.2: perhaps you can find something of use from it?
wytr.dialog.Wedyf.10.9.f0d71690.3: Killing enemies in the Nesaak region may be worth your time, as well.
wytr.dialog.Wedyf.1.1.e20c5553: How is your quest coming along? I am still waiting for the items I asked of you.
wytr.dialog.Wedyf.6.2.76b2fad8: Although... I might have forgot to tell you about something else too...
wytr.dialog.Wedyf.6.3.c0e2323c: We also need a part of the soul of your dead friend.
wytr.dialog.Wedyf.6.4.9996a461.1: This is something I unfortunately cannot do myself. There is
wytr.dialog.Wedyf.6.4.9996a461.3: who does this kind of stuff.
wytr.dialog.Wedyf.6.5.c28f36e4.1: He can extract the soul from someone's weapon. Very useful in those situations.
wytr.dialog.Wedyf.6.6.bef826fb: Bring me the soul, and I'll be able to remove the spell preventing you from entering the tomb.
wytr.dialog.Wedyf.1.1.150942a4: Welcome back to our humble little town!
wytr.dialog.TheBlacksmith.8.1.7800110b: What can I do for ya?
wytr.dialog.TheBlacksmith.8.2.0d0c695f: Oh yes! I can extract the soul from weapons!
wytr.dialog.TheBlacksmith.8.3.58f072ce.1: Bring me the weapons of your friend,
wytr.dialog.TheBlacksmith.8.3.58f072ce.2: and I'll see if I can do something with it!
wytr.dialog.TheBlacksmith.8.4.58518ff5: Oh it's... those weapons. Well, if you know what you're doing...
wytr.dialog.TheBlacksmith.8.6.ff643317.1: Be careful with the weapons, you will only get
wytr.dialog.TheBlacksmith.8.6.ff643317.3: of each. If you lose one, you will have to ask around if anyone has a spare.
wytr.dialog.TheBlacksmith.8.7.2e9209fe: Maybe someone will be selling one on the Trade Market in Detlas, who knows.
wytr.dialog.TheBlacksmith.8.8.c5079038: Anyway, my apprentice over there has traveled around a lot, they might know where you can find the items for yourself, but I warn you, they are a little bit quirky.
wytr.dialog.TheBlacksmith.2.1.099b23cc.9: so I can extract the soul from them.
wytr.dialog.TheBlacksmith.2.2.9abeffae: Think you can get those from monsters somewhere 'round Nesaak.
wytr.dialog.Apprentice.6.1.11d82e28: Weapons of the depressed kind? Oh, of course, of course, I know of the set! Around Nesaak, I hear they are kept.
wytr.dialog.Apprentice.6.2.db1ffbfe: An army of Linx you must clear, in a cave you shall find this spear!
wytr.dialog.Apprentice.6.3.19c1a31c: To a skilled archer you must go, best her in a lumberyard and you will have her bow!
wytr.dialog.Apprentice.6.4.56d4a2e2: On an altar, effervescence leers, complete the sacrifice and you will gain your shears...
wytr.dialog.Apprentice.6.5.f087c42b: In the forest, a house frozen in spikes thick, outsmart the contraption and be gifted a stick!
wytr.dialog.Apprentice.6.6.d0abb4f6: But beware, beware! Danger lies ahead, and will try to halt you in your stead!
wytr.dialog.MarkqueTheWizard.8.2.d328361: I've just been hangin' down here working on my teleportation device. The teleporters got partially frozen over, but I'm pretty damn sure they still work.
wytr.dialog.MarkqueTheWizard.8.3.4a2dd72: Hey, if you want to test it out, be my guest! You can use the teleporter core next to me to start it.
wytr.dialog.MarkqueTheWizard.8.4.3273fa2: Right click with it while on the center of the iced over teleporter chamber, and it will teleport you in a direction over to the next chamber.
wytr.dialog.MarkqueTheWizard.8.5.2e88227: It will then teleport you again in a direction 90 degrees clockwise, and it will keep doin' that forever.
wytr.dialog.MarkqueTheWizard.8.6.516d6ec: Some of the ice walls have holes in them, and I believe if you use the teleporter core correctly you will be able to make it to the other side where the gold platform is.
wytr.dialog.MarkqueTheWizard.8.7.79f72ff: The core is unstable, though, and it will break if you run too far away. Keep that in mind, yeah?
wytr.dialog.MarkqueTheWizard.8.8.31e551f: Oh, and I left an old wand of mine down at the gold platform. The thing was very depressing, though, so it ain't too much of an issue. But hey, if you can get to it, it's all yours, bud, free of cost!
wytr.dialog.TheBlacksmith.4.1.7bf11e94: ... Hi again. I see you got the weapons.
wytr.dialog.TheBlacksmith.4.2.281a3da3: These weapons emanate so much sadness... I'm sure you heard about Bob's story...
wytr.dialog.TheBlacksmith.4.3.34c9f6b2: Here is the soul. It's a little bit crushed, but it can do the trick.
wytr.dialog.TheBlacksmith.4.4.9cc48beb: Good luck on your quest. Bob was a great hero, anything to help him is good in my book.
wytr.dialog.TheBlacksmith.1.1.649900d5: What can I do for ya?
wytr.dialog.Wedyf.6.1.10821e78: I'm glad to see you again.
wytr.dialog.Wedyf.6.2.f416990c: I only need a part of the soul, you can keep the rest.
wytr.dialog.Wedyf.6.3.8304db5e: Give me a minute, I need to concentrate...
wytr.dialog.Wedyf.6.6.1b5de50a.2: You should be able to enter the tomb now.
wytr.text.ea805ffca4b3e41b266a7087ad454b: As you open the door, you feel some soft wind running past you. The lamentations have stopped...
wytr.dialog.Tarod.3.1.b10cd02b: You're back... Has he... has he finally been put to rest?
wytr.dialog.Tarod.3.2.3110987c.1: It's... hard to hear, knowing that my old friend is
wytr.dialog.Tarod.3.2.3110987c.3: gone, this time, but... I'm happy he won't have to suffer on this war-torn world for another second.
wytr.dialog.Tarod.3.3.df1d1c51: ...I want you to have something. This is his old battle chesplate; he gave it to me a few days before he vanished. I think if he were still here, he'd want you to have this. Please, take good care of it for me...
wytr.dialog.Tarod.1.1.ea4ff2e4: Thank you for your help. I'm sure Bob thanks you too... wherever he is.
